			var src ="//in.bmscdn.com/iedb/movies/images/website/banner/large/malaal-et00102891-15-05-2019-09-34-57.jpg", imgSrc = "//in.bmscdn.com/iedb/movies/images/website/poster/large/malaal-et00102891-15-05-2019-09-34-57.jpg";			function fnChangeUrl(pathName) {
				try {
					var myURL = window.location.pathname.substr(0, window.location.pathname.indexOf("movies"));
					window.location = myURL+"movies/"+pathName;
				} catch(e) {
					BMS.Misc.fnErr({ fnName : "fnChangeUrl", err : e });
				}
			}

                        						<div id="mv-summary" class="tab-content" style="display: none;">
                                                    <div class="__heading">SYNOPSIS</div>
                            <div class="synopsis">
                               <blockquote cite="http://in.bookmyshow.com/movies/malaal/ET00102891">
									A contemporary love story between Astha and Shiva, who are from contrasting backgrounds living in a Mumbai chawl, Malaal is a romantic drama film which is the remake of Tamil film 7G Rainbow Colony. Produced by Sanjay Leela Bhansali, Bhushan Kumar, Mahaveer Jain and Krishan Kumar, Maalal stars  debutants Sharmin Segal and Meezaan Jaffrey in lead roles.								</blockquote>
                            </div>

	<span class="__timestamp">7/7/19</span>									  </span></div><div class="__reviewer-text">well..the movie revolves around boy and girl who are from different social strata but somehow get to stay in the same chawl.they develop instant bond which graduates into deep love  however they cannot unite assumably due to girls reservations and love towards her family.First half just passes by and one just keep wishing that the story gets a push through some character.2nd half moves the story a bit ahead but again without any covers to unlayer.There is a hint of a influential political group which keeps everyone guessing to enter the plot and give story some chances to breathe but it doesn't take place.The ending is a big timelapse which does not look convincing.Rookie Meezan has  lacks persona which a SLB movie protagonists normally have.The girl doesn't look smooth and sometimes you wonder if this is the thing you like in her.The movie is set in late nineties and SLB has used a couple of movies and songs to depict same.Meezan also scores 2 and sharmin will get 2.5 ,however one is still in dilemma that the character wanted sharmin to be a bit disconnected or it's her own personna.overall a 2 out of 5 star.</div></div></div><div class="mv-synopsis-review"><div class="__reviewer-face"><div class="wow __reviewer-image-area" style="visibility: visible;"><img impact to pull the audience...The only hope was that it was produced by Sanjay Leela Bhansali who would not put his money on a movie which is not worth watching..

The movie from its first scene will start connecting with you and as the movie progresses scene by scene it will start gripping you..The movie is a PURE BLISS..
Its so Soulful that you will feel that you are listening a beautiful song..The Director has done a Tremendous Job..The editing rhythms with the movie..The songs are not catchy and you might not even remember them after coming out but in between the movie you will feel a connect listening to them..There are 3 scenes in the movie which i am sure no body has ever watched in a movie for which director and writter must be applauded.. However after saying all above the best part of the movie is its Lead Star Cast (Meezan Jaffery &amp; Sharmin Segal)...Both looks amazing and have done a Fabulous work in there Debue Movie..Specially Meezan Jaffery who is simply mesmerizing..A New Star Kid has arrived who is here to Stay..

						<a href="/mumbai/movies/malaal/ET00102891" itemprop="url">
							<span itemprop="title">Malaal</span>
						</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
                    </section>

        	var infoClickHandler = function () {
        		var event_code = $(this).attr("data-id");
        		var event_title = $(this).attr("data-event-title");

				BMS.Misc.fnPushEventDataToAnalytics(["GA"], "", {}, {

					'movie_id': event_code,
					'position': position,
					'movie_name': event_title
				});
        	};

        	var eType = "MT" ;
